children.name: Rules
children.text:
This +1 Greatsword is made from the jaws of a draconic skeleton, and contains the hunger of Eravoros.
As a bonus action the wielder of this blade can sacrifice 2d6 hit points to the blade, taking that much damage without any resistances or immunity. Their next attack with this blade that hits deals an extra 2d6 points of damage. This can be used a number of times per day equal to the wielder's Constitution Modifier + the wielder's Proficiency Bonus. If this damage reduces them to zero hit points, they die instantly and are consumed by the sword. This makes the sword become +2 for a year. This bonus can stack up to +4. 
At the end of the year, it returns to its normal state.
